---

<div id='research-section' data-link-name='Research' class='section mt-12'>
  <div id='research-header' class='font-display w-full h-6 mb-12 border-b border-slate-700'>
    <span class='text-4xl font-bold bg-gray-100 pr-10'>
      Research
    </span>
  </div>
  <div id='research-interest-container' data-link-name='Research Interest' class='sub-section mb-6'>
    <h3 class='text-2xl mb-3 font-display underline'>Research Interest</h3>
    <p>
      While at San Diego State, my main interest was in algebraic
      combinatorics. In particular, I studied relationships between numerical
      semigroups and polytopes under <a href='https://cdoneill.sdsu.edu/' class='transition duration-150 underline hover:text-sky-500'>Dr. Christopher O'Neill</a>. I also
      participated in 
      <a href='https://www.slmath.org/msri-up#description_msri_up'
         class='transition duration-150 underline hover:text-sky-500'>MSRI-UP</a>
      where I had the opportunity to work with a combinatorial connection with Lie
      algebras under <a href='https://www.pamelaeharris.com/' class='transition duration-150 underline hover:text-sky-500'>Dr. Pamela E. Harris</a>. Now, under my advisor <a href='https://www-users.cse.umn.edu/~cberkesc/' class='transition duration-150 underline hover:text-sky-500'>Dr. Christine Berkesch</a>, my main interests lie in commutative algebra and algebraic geometry. In particular, my interest at the moment is studying characterizations of ideals by using differential operators of the ring that the ideal lives in.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div id='publications-container' data-link-name='Publications' class='sub-section'>
